- Python has a very unique feature knows as "interactive mode" . 
- In this mode you can dynamically input the code inside the terminal and get output right after hitting enter.
- To go into interactive mode, you will have to go inside terminal and enter " python ".
- This input inside terminal will result in a small change a ' >>> ' arrow will appear inside the terminal. 
- This tells you that the terminal is now in interactive mode, now proceed typing any code inside terminal it will give output below the input.

- For example:  >>> 1 + 1 
                  2
              
              >>> print("Hello World")
                  Hello World